cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to predict blood glucose levels in diabetic patients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of domain knowledge to construct a parsimonious deep representation, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
